# gBlockParty - Deployment Platform Specification

**Author:** George Le | **Date:** February 2026 | **Status:** Final Specification

---

## Executive Summary

gBlockParty is an internal deployment platform for a solo developer that provides GitHub-connected hosting, auto-deploy on push, preview URLs per PR, environment management, and database provisioning. It deploys Next.js apps (static and server-rendered) and arbitrary Dockerized backend services.

The platform runs on a Hetzner VPS with Cloudflare CDN/DNS and AWS RDS Postgres, replacing Vercel (free tier) and Neon ($20/mo) while maintaining cost-neutral total infrastructure spend (~$274/mo including existing Bismarck AWS costs).

