## 1. Goals & Non-Goals

### Goals

- **Push-to-deploy**: Push to main branch triggers automatic build and deployment
- **Preview deployments**: Every PR gets a live preview URL with bot comments
- **Next.js first-class support**: Both static export and full server mode (SSR, API routes, middleware, server actions)
- **Backend service support**: Deploy arbitrary Dockerized Node.js (and other) backend services
- **Database provisioning**: Replace Neon with self-managed RDS Postgres, with a dashboard UI to create databases
- **Environment management**: Per-environment (production/preview) env vars managed via dashboard and CLI
- **Rollback**: One-click rollback to any of the last 10 deployments
- **Monorepo support**: Deploy specific services from monorepos
- **Cost-neutral**: Total infrastructure cost stays ~$274/mo (matching current Bismarck + Neon spend)

### Non-Goals (Out of Scope)

- **Multi-tenancy**: No team/org support, no RBAC, no user management beyond the owner
- **Billing/metering**: No usage tracking, no pricing tiers, no Stripe integration
- **Custom domains**: Deferred to a later phase; MVP uses platform subdomains only
- **Multi-cloud deployment**: MVP deploys to VPS only; provider abstraction designed in for future Azure/Cloudflare support
- **Bismarck migration**: Deferred; platform should eventually be capable of hosting Bismarck but this is not an MVP goal
- **Public-facing signup**: No registration flow; GitHub OAuth restricted to the owner's account

