## 2. Architecture Overview

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                     CLOUDFLARE                            │
│  DNS (*.yourdomain.dev → VPS IP)                         │
│  CDN (caches static assets at edge)                      │
│  SSL termination (free, automatic)                       │
└──────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────┘
                   │ HTTPS
┌──────────────────▼───────────────────────────────────────┐
│                   HETZNER VPS (CX32)                      │
│              4 vCPU | 8 GB RAM | 80 GB disk               │
│                                                           │
│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │
│  │  CADDY (Reverse Proxy)                               │ │
│  │  Routes by hostname → Docker containers              │ │
│  └──────────┬──────────────────────────────────────────┘ │
│             │                                             │
│  ┌──────────▼──────────────────────────────────────────┐ │
│  │  DOCKER CONTAINERS                                   │ │
│  │                                                       │ │
│  │  [Platform Control Plane + Dashboard]                 │ │
│  │    Next.js app (API routes + UI)                      │ │
│  │    Handles: webhooks, deployments, auth, dashboard    │ │
│  │                                                       │ │
│  │  [App: myapp (production)]     port 3001              │ │
│  │  [App: myapi (production)]     port 3002              │ │
│  │  [App: myapp (PR #42)]         port 4001              │ │
│  │  [App: myapp (PR #43)]         port 4002              │ │
│  │  ...                                                  │ │
│  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
         │                          │
         │ AWS SDK                  │ pg connection (SSL)
         ▼                          ▼
┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────────────┐
│  AWS S3          │    │  AWS RDS Postgres        │
│  Build cache     │    │  db.t4g.micro ($13/mo)   │
│  Build logs      │    │  Platform DB + App DBs   │
└─────────────────┘    └─────────────────────────┘
         │
         ▼
┌─────────────────┐
│  AWS Secrets Mgr │
│  API keys, creds │
└─────────────────┘
```

### Technology Stack

| Component | Technology | Why |
|-----------|-----------|-----|
| CDN / DNS / SSL | Cloudflare (free tier) | Free, automatic SSL, global CDN, wildcard DNS |
| VPS | Hetzner CX32 (US East) | $7/mo, 4 vCPU, 8 GB RAM, close to AWS us-east-1 |
| Reverse proxy | Caddy | Simple config, admin API for dynamic reloads, static file serving |
| Container runtime | Docker | Industry standard, good isolation, easy image management |
| Control plane + Dashboard | Next.js (TypeScript) | Dogfooded on the platform, SSR + API routes in one |
| Database (platform) | PostgreSQL on RDS | Shared instance with app databases, reliable, automated backups |
| Database (apps) | PostgreSQL on RDS | Same instance, separate databases per app |
| Build cache | AWS S3 | Cheap, durable, accessible from VPS via AWS SDK |
| Secrets | AWS Secrets Manager | Consistent with Bismarck, native encryption, audit trail |
| Build logs | S3 (long-term) + streaming via WebSocket | |
| Auth | GitHub OAuth (via GitHub App) | Single sign-on, no separate auth system |
| Notifications | GitHub commit status + Slack/Discord webhooks | |
| CLI | TypeScript / Node.js (Commander.js) | Same language as platform |
| Package manager | pnpm | Primary; detect from lockfile |
| IaC | Terraform (base infra only) | RDS, S3, Secrets Manager provisioned via Terraform |

### Provider Abstraction

The codebase includes a `DeploymentProvider` interface to support future multi-cloud deployment:

```typescript
interface DeploymentProvider {
  createService(config: ServiceConfig): Promise<Service>;
  updateService(serviceId: string, config: ServiceConfig): Promise<Service>;
  deleteService(serviceId: string): Promise<void>;
  getServiceStatus(serviceId: string): Promise<ServiceStatus>;
  getLogs(serviceId: string, options: LogOptions): AsyncIterable<string>;
  rollback(serviceId: string, targetDeploymentId: string): Promise<Service>;
}
```

MVP implements `DockerProvider` (manages containers on the VPS via Docker API). Future providers: `AWSECSProvider`, `AzureContainerAppsProvider`, `CloudflareProvider`.

